<h1>How To Match Your Socks To Your Outfit?</h1>

Are you troubled thinking "what" to match your socks with: the shoes? The pants? The jacket? Or something else?<br />
 <br />
Well, if this problem affects you, too, here is the answer. Generally advance you that, as the tie must be harmonized with the top of your figure and then his shirt, jacket, and not least with the color of your face, your socks should bind primarily to the lower part of your body, thus with shoes and pants.<br />
<br />
<strong>But precise: </strong>only primarily, that is, as a general rule, since your socks can also tune with the color of your tie, your shirt, or your shirt, but step by step. Are four things or the ways you need to know to choose and match your socks:<br />
Always choose stockings that cover you the calf.<br />
You can make a classic combination, making sure that the color of the <a class="ext" href="https://www.socksfromhell.com/the-ultimate-guide-to-buying-socks/">Happy Socks</a><span class="exttail">&#8734;</span> gets along with shoes, pants and jacket.<br />
You can make a more fashionable combination, matching your socks to the color of the tie, shirt or vest.<br />
The classic combination is perhaps the most obvious, but this is the easiest and adaptable, because it is a perfect system for any occasion: work, leisure, special occasion, at the ceremony. It is expected that the color of your stockings are always in tone mainly with the color of the shoe, but which at the same time takes into account the color of the pants and possibly also that of the jacket. Here are some examples:<br />
<br />
If you are dressed all in blue, your shoe must be black, dark brown or dark brown and your socks in both cases (ie, either black shoe brown) must be very dark blue. If you are dressed in gray, your shoes will be either black or dark brown, but this time, the socks must be very dark gray. But if you wear a blue jacket with beige trousers and a brown shoe, your shoes should be dark blue as the jacket and in any way, nor ever beige or brown.<br />
<br />
If you fancy something different, that gives your look a touch of style, then you can try a color link between the socks and tie, or shirt or jersey. Not necessarily the color should be plain, type: red sock with red tie. But you can also buy funky socks online with small drawings to create a lure with the color of the tie, then:<br />
<br />
<ul><li> Tie plain and striped socks or small patterns of the same color on a dark background (gray, blue, brown)
</li><li> Patterned tie and sock in solid colors of the prevailing color in the tie.
</li><li> Colored knit plain (eg. Green) and striped socks or micro - patterned in shades of green.</li></ul>
The combination with the shirt only applies if the shirt is dark, for example: blue, purple, gray, black or otherwise if it is of an intense color. In short not worth combine clear stockings if your shirt is clear; in this case stick to the color of the shoe and the trousers.<br />

